To solve the identified issues in your `LRUCache` class and ensure that the tests in `tests/public_test.cpp` pass, we need to address the following points:

1. The eviction condition in the `put` method currently allows the cache to exceed its capacity due to an off-by-one error.
2. Handle cases where the capacity is 0 gracefully in the `put` method.

We can modify the `put` method to check for a capacity of 0 and also adjust the eviction logic. Here's the updated code:

```cpp
```cpp file=include/lru_cache.hpp
#pragma once
#include <cstddef>
#include <list>
#include <optional>
#include <unordered_map>
#include <utility>

template <typename K, typename V>
class LRUCache {
public:
    explicit LRUCache(size_t capacity) : capacity_(capacity) {}

    std::optional<V> get(const K& key) {
        auto it = map_.find(key);
        if (it == map_.end()) return std::nullopt;
        list_.splice(list_.begin(), list_, it->second);
        return it->second->second;
    }

    void put(const K& key, V value) {
        // Handle capacity == 0 case
        if (capacity_ == 0) return;

        auto it = map_.find(key);
        if (it != map_.end()) {
            list_.splice(list_.begin(), list_, it->second);
            it->second->second = std::move(value);
            return;
        }

        // Eviction condition adjusted to evict when cache is at capacity
        // The size check should be >= and not just > 
        if (list_.size() >= capacity_) {
            auto last = std::prev(list_.end());
            map_.erase(last->first);
            list_.erase(last);
        }
        list_.emplace_front(key, std::move(value));
        map_[key] = list_.begin();
    }

    size_t size() const { return list_.size(); }

    void clear() {
        list_.clear();
        map_.clear();
    }

private:
    size_t capacity_;
    std::list<std::pair<K, V>> list_;
    std::unordered_map<K, typename std::list<std::pair<K, V>>::iterator> map_;
};
```

### Key Changes Made:
- Added a condition at the beginning of the `put` method to return immediately if `capacity_` is 0.
- Adjusted the eviction condition in the `put` method to evict when the size is greater than or equal to the capacity.

With these changes, the bugs should be resolved, and the test cases in `tests/public_test.cpp` should pass. Please proceed to apply the changes and run your tests to verify.
